4 (1) No person shall buy, sell, trade, traffic, or process eggs in Kentucky without a
5 license issued pursuant to the egg marketing law, with the following exceptions:
6 (a) Hatcheries purchasing eggs to be used exclusively for hatching purposes;
7 (b) Hotels, restaurants, and other eating places where all eggs purchased are
8 served in the establishment;
9 (c) Bakeries, confectioneries, and ice cream manufacturers who use eggs in a
10 manufactured product;
11 (d) Consumers buying eggs for their own consumption; or
12 (e) Producers who sell only directly to consumers and do not exceed a sales limit
13 of two hundred forty (240)[sixty (60)] dozen eggs per calendar week.
14 (2) Any person engaged in the act of selling shell eggs or egg products under any of the
15 following circumstances shall have all shell eggs and egg products placed under a
16 stop order:
17 (a) Selling or otherwise marketing shell eggs or egg products without a license;
18 (b) Selling or otherwise marketing shell eggs or egg products without first
19 submitting an emergency recall plan to the department; or
20 (c) Failing to remit or pay fines owed to the department.
21 (3) Any person engaged in the act of selling or otherwise marketing shell eggs under
22 the following conditions shall have those eggs placed under a stop order for:
23 (a) Failing to have the proper labels attached, as required by KRS 260.630; or
24 (b) Failing to meet the tolerances of consumer grades and consumer grade quality
25 standards, as required by KRS 260.620.
26 (4) Any person engaged in the act of selling or otherwise marketing shell eggs or egg
27 products shall have these shell eggs or egg products placed under a withdraw from
